OL,3,CMiners' strike: Life on the picket
OL,4,Cline from the people who were there
OL,6,FDave Temple was 40 in March 1984. A
OL,7,FDurham miner, married with children.
OL,9,F"I knew there was no alternative," he
OL,10,Fsaid. "We came out on strike first.
OL,12,F"The first thing that we did was to go
OL,13,Fdown Woods Terrace. There were several
OL,14,Fbutcher shops there and we begged
OL,15,Ffood. We were going to make sheep's
OL,16,Fhead broth and they collected all the
OL,17,Fbones and everything like that and
OL,18,Fmade some broth.
OL,20,F"I had a mortgage. I'd bought a pit
OL,21,Fhouse. I had no money. Nothing.
