OL,3,CMiners' strike: Life on the picket
OL,4,Cline from the people who were there
OL,6,F"There was two main forces in this
OL,7,Fstrike. The young lads.J"And there was
OL,8,Fthe women. They were tremendous
OL,9,Fbecause they fed us."
OL,11,FCharlie Bell was a miner for 20 years.
OL,12,FHe told ITV Tyne Tees: "We didn't even
OL,13,Fthink it would last months, let alone
OL,14,Fa year. It was going to be difficult.
OL,15,FAnd was it difficult.
OL,17,F"Retired miners were still around to
OL,18,Fhelp and support. You could walk down
OL,19,Fthe street and everybody faced the
OL,20,Fsame problems. It's quite a beautiful
OL,21,Fthing. We're all in it together."
