OL,3,CMiners' strike: Life on the picket
OL,4,Cline from the people who were there
OL,6,FHe said: "I can't forgive them even to
OL,7,Fthis day. It's 40 years on and they've
OL,8,Fgot a lot of questions to answer."
OL,10,FThe miners played a long game and
OL,11,Ffought a hard fight but in August
OL,12,F1984, the first North East miner - 'a
OL,13,Fscab'- crossed the picket line in
OL,14,FEasington.
OL,16,FMr Temple explained: "We used to say
OL,17,Fwe're poor, but we won't always be
OL,18,Fpoor. You're a scab and you'll always
OL,19,Fbe a scab."
