OL,3,CMiners' strike: Life on the picket
OL,4,Cline from the people who were there
OL,6,F"They were beat but they didn't stop
OL,7,Fbelieving we were right."
OL,9,FThe miners voted to return to work in
OL,10,FMarch 1985 - almost a year after they
OL,11,Fwalked out- and it was that return
OL,12,Fthat marked the beginning of the end
OL,13,Fof centuries of coal mining in the
OL,14,Fregion.
OL,16,FDozens of miners marched into the pit
OL,17,Fin tears - their bitterness at losing
OL,18,Ftheir war.
OL,20,FBut all of them stand by their reasons
OL,21,Ffor striking.
